# Robots should be blocked either (1) by headers.html, or (2) by robots.html,
# but not both. Ignore whichever is not used.

# If we ARE hosting on Netlify, headers.html will block robots,
# so we should ignore robots.html (by uncommenting the next line)
# src/files/robots.html

# If we ARE NOT hosting on Netlify, robots.html will block robots,
# (unless we use HTTP headers in a server config or PHP file, etc.),
# so we should ignore headers.html (by uncommenting the next line)
src/files/headers.html